Deputy President William Ruto this morning will host elected leaders and aspirants ahead of a similar meeting by Cord at the Bomas of Kenya tomorrow.The 7am meeting will be at Ruto&rsquo;s Karen residence and more than 5,000 leaders are expected. The DP&rsquo;s communications director David Mugonyi confirmed it will take place, without disclosing the agenda. However, sources close to the DP said it will cover nominations and voter registration starting next week. Participants will be briefed on preparations for the presidential campaign.The DP is expected to urge them to support election amendments, which the opposition rejects. They allow manual backup in voter identification and results transmission if electronic systems fail. The opposition says this will enable rigging. Within JP there are suspicions, infighting and fears of unfair, bungled nominations, and fears of losing the parliamentary majority.